ss/dynamic-access-coverage.json` is `hasDynamicAccess: false` with `0/0` calls, so the automation never turned the passing test into a complete `library-new-request` submission.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.grpc:grpc-alts:1.68.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T08-05-07-166650Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.grpc:grpc-alts:1.68.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T08-07-56-708539Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.grpc:grpc-alts:1.68.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T08-11-45-824004Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.grpc:grpc-alts:1.68.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T08-31-43-905394Z.log`\n- `stats/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/execution-metrics.json`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Decide whether `grpc-alts` should be accepted as a `0/0` dynamic-access case; if yes, add the missing `metadata/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json` (likely `{}`) and the expected stats artifact(s).\n2. Review whether the Netty `tcnative`/OpenSSL workaround in `tests/src/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/build.gradle` is acceptable for long-term support of this library.\n3. Rerun the library-specific validation after the metadata/stats artifacts are in place."}}
